#Define categories for analysis

# Check dataset after imputation and reimport. Removed column 1 from complete
# csv file and edit headings if req
D3 <- read.csv("Complete.csv")

view(D3)

# Dataset categories are represented as 1 - heterosexual females, 2 -
# heterosexual males, 3 - LGBTQ+
D4 <- D3 %>%
    select(!Category)

Female_hetero <- D3 %>%
    filter(Category == 1) %>%
    select(!Category)

Male_hetero <- D3 %>%
    filter(Category == 2) %>%
    select(!Category)

LGBTQ <- D3 %>%
    filter(Category == 3) %>%
    select(!Category)

#Define groups and legend for nodes

groups1 <- list(BYSAS = c(1:6), DASS21 = c(7:13))
Names <- c("Think about sex", "Increased sexual urges", "Use sex to escape", "Unsuccessfully reduce sex",
    "Troubled if prohibited from sex", "Sex has negative impact", "dryness of mouth",
    "breathing difficulties", "experienced trembling", "worried I might panic", "close to panic",
    "aware of heartbeat", "scared without reason")

#Plot Bridge symptoms

## Prepping male_hetero data frame
graph_males <- qgraph::EBICglasso(cor(Male_hetero), n=dim(Male_hetero)[1])
 b_males <- bridge(graph_males, communities = groups1)
 Strength_m <-  b_males$`Bridge Strength`

 Expect_m <-  b_males$`Bridge Expected Influence (1-step)`
Bsymptoms_m <- Male_hetero%>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(1:13), names_to = "symptoms", values_to = "n")%>%
  select(symptoms) %>%
  slice_head(n=13)

 symptoms_m <- tibble::tibble(
  Bsymptoms_m,
  Strength_m,

  Expect_m
) %>%
  mutate(
    `Bridge strength` = (Strength_m - mean(Strength_m)) / sd(Strength_m),
 
    `Bridge expect inf` = (Expect_m - mean(Expect_m)) / sd(Expect_m)
  ) %>%
  tidyr::pivot_longer(
    cols = c(Strength_m,  Expect_m),
    names_to = "Bcent",
    values_to = "n"
  )

## Prepping female_hetero data frame
graph_females <- qgraph::EBICglasso(cor(Female_hetero), n=dim(Female_hetero)[1])
b_females <- bridge(graph_females, communities = groups1)
Strength_f <- b_females$`Bridge Strength`

Expect_f <- b_females$`Bridge Expected Influence (1-step)`
Bsymptoms_f <- Female_hetero%>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(1:13), names_to = "symptoms", values_to = "n")%>%
  select(symptoms) %>%
  slice_head(n=13)


symptoms_f <- tibble::tibble(
  Bsymptoms_f,
  Strength_f,
 
  Expect_f
) %>%
  mutate(
    `Bridge strength` = (Strength_f - mean(Strength_f)) / sd(Strength_f),
   
    `Bridge expect inf` = (Expect_f - mean(Expect_f)) / sd(Expect_f)
  ) %>%
  tidyr::pivot_longer(
    cols = c(Strength_f, Expect_f),
    names_to = "Bcent",
    values_to = "n"
  )

## Prepping LGBTQ data frame
graph_LGBTQ <- qgraph::EBICglasso(cor(LGBTQ), n=dim(LGBTQ)[1])
b_LGBTQ <- bridge(graph_LGBTQ, communities = groups1)
Strength_L <- b_LGBTQ$`Bridge Strength`

Expect_L <- b_LGBTQ$`Bridge Expected Influence (1-step)`
Bsymptoms_L <- LGBTQ%>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(1:13), names_to = "symptoms", values_to = "n")%>%
  select(symptoms) %>%
  slice_head(n=13)

symptoms_L <- tibble::tibble(
  Bsymptoms_L,
  Strength_L,

  Expect_L
) %>%
  mutate(
    `Bridge strength` = (Strength_L - mean(Strength_L)) / sd(Strength_L),
    
    `Bridge expect inf` = (Expect_L - mean(Expect_L)) / sd(Expect_L)
  ) %>%
  tidyr::pivot_longer(
    cols = c(Strength_L,  Expect_L),
    names_to = "Bcent",
    values_to = "n"
  )
